Considering Squamous Cell Carcinoma
    1. A long-term unhealed ulcer on the outer side of the left buttock, with a medical history of 2 years;
    2. The surface of the ulcer is granular and cauliflower-like;
    This already meets the clinical diagnosis of skin squamous cell carcinoma.
    However, a final diagnosis still requires a pathological examination.

